---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="BlackPink Trading Team Case Study" lang="en" currentPath="/guide/blackpink-case" description="How the BlackPink team uses OpenClaw with 4 specialized AI personas to run a crypto trading operation.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge badge-orange">Case Study</span>
      <h1>The BlackPink Trading Team</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Four people. Four specialized AI personas. One OpenClaw gateway. Here's how they run a crypto trading operation entirely from their phones.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Overview -->
      <section class="article-section">
        <div class="overview-box">
          <div class="overview-stat">
            <span class="ov-num">4</span>
            <span class="ov-label">Team Members</span>
          </div>
          <div class="overview-stat">
            <span class="ov-num">4</span>
            <span class="ov-label">AI Personas</span>
          </div>
          <div class="overview-stat">
            <span class="ov-num">1</span>
            <span class="ov-label">OpenClaw Gateway</span>
          </div>
          <div class="overview-stat">
            <span class="ov-num">24/7</span>
            <span class="ov-label">Always On</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Team Intro -->
      <section class="article-section">
        <h2>Meet the Team</h2>
        <p>
          The BlackPink team is a small, tight-knit group of traders and analysts who specialize in crypto markets.
          They don't work in an office ‚Äî they operate fully remotely, coordinating via Telegram group chats and relying
          heavily on their AI-powered tools to stay ahead of the market. Each team member has a dedicated OpenClaw
          workspace with a persona tuned for their specific role.
        </p>

        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-member-card">
            <div class="member-header">
              <div class="member-avatar">üåπ</div>
              <div>
                <div class="member-name">Ros√©</div>
                <div class="member-title">Lead Strategist & Quant Bot Manager</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="member-desc">
              Ros√© manages the team's flagship algorithmic trading bot ‚Äî Hydra. She's the one who writes and refines the
              bot's trading strategies, monitors its performance, and decides when to intervene manually. Her AI persona
              acts as a quant analysis partner and bot co-pilot.
            </p>
            <div class="member-ai-role">
              <span class="role-badge">AI Role:</span> Hydra bot monitor, strategy advisor, Python code reviewer
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="team-member-card">
            <div class="member-header">
              <div class="member-avatar">üíÉ</div>
              <div>
                <div class="member-name">Lisa</div>
                <div class="member-title">Technical Analyst</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="member-desc">
              Lisa lives in chart patterns and price action. She focuses on technical analysis across multiple timeframes,
              identifying entry/exit signals for the team. Her AI persona is trained to think in terms of support/resistance,
              momentum indicators, and pattern recognition.
            </p>
            <div class="member-ai-role">
              <span class="role-badge">AI Role:</span> Chart pattern analysis, indicator interpretation, signal generation
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="team-member-card">
            <div class="member-header">
              <div class="member-avatar">üå∏</div>
              <div>
                <div class="member-name">Jisoo</div>
                <div class="member-title">News & Market Intelligence</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="member-desc">
              Jisoo monitors the information landscape ‚Äî news, social sentiment, on-chain data, regulatory updates.
              She synthesizes large volumes of information into actionable intelligence. Her AI persona is a skilled
              researcher and summarizer with deep crypto market context.
            </p>
            <div class="member-ai-role">
              <span class="role-badge">AI Role:</span> News summarization, sentiment analysis, regulatory research
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="team-member-card">
            <div class="member-header">
              <div class="member-avatar">üíé</div>
              <div>
                <div class="member-name">Jennie</div>
                <div class="member-title">Portfolio Manager & Risk Officer</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="member-desc">
              Jennie oversees the portfolio's overall health. She manages position sizing, monitors risk exposure,
              enforces stop-loss discipline, and ensures the team doesn't blow up chasing signals. Her AI is a
              conservative, numbers-focused risk analyst.
            </p>
            <div class="member-ai-role">
              <span class="role-badge">AI Role:</span> Risk calculations, portfolio rebalancing, drawdown analysis
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What They're Doing -->
      <section class="article-section">
        <h2>The Operation: What They're Actually Running</h2>

        <div class="operation-cards">
          <div class="op-card">
            <div class="op-header">
              <div class="op-icon">ü§ñ</div>
              <div class="op-title">Hydra Trading Bot</div>
            </div>
            <p>
              Hydra is an algorithmic trading bot running on a VPS, executing trades on crypto exchanges based on
              programmatic strategies. Ros√©'s OpenClaw instance connects directly to the bot's monitoring system.
              She can ask her AI things like <em>"What's Hydra's P&L this week?"</em> or <em>"Check if the BTC momentum
              strategy is within normal parameters"</em> ‚Äî and get instant analysis.
            </p>
            <div class="op-persona">
              <strong>Powered by:</strong> Ros√©'s persona (quant + Python + trading systems expertise)
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="op-card">
            <div class="op-header">
              <div class="op-icon">üìä</div>
              <div class="op-title">Real-Time Market Analysis</div>
            </div>
            <p>
              Lisa queries her AI throughout the trading day. She'll share a chart screenshot and ask for confluence
              analysis, or describe a pattern and ask what the historical win rate is for that setup. The persona has
              been tuned with Lisa's preferred indicators (EMA ribbons, RSI divergence, volume profile) so responses
              are immediately relevant.
            </p>
            <div class="op-persona">
              <strong>Powered by:</strong> Lisa's persona (technical analysis specialist)
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="op-card">
            <div class="op-header">
              <div class="op-icon">üì∞</div>
              <div class="op-title">News Intelligence Pipeline</div>
            </div>
            <p>
              Jisoo uses her AI to rapidly process news. She'll paste in an article and ask "How might this affect
              ETH in the next 48 hours?" or "Give me 5 bullet points on the key risk factors from this Fed speech."
              The persona understands crypto-macro connections and gives analysis in minutes instead of hours.
            </p>
            <div class="op-persona">
              <strong>Powered by:</strong> Jisoo's persona (macro research + market intelligence)
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="op-card">
            <div class="op-header">
              <div class="op-icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
              <div class="op-title">Risk Management Dashboard</div>
            </div>
            <p>
              Jennie checks in with her AI multiple times per day. She'll send the current portfolio snapshot and get
              a risk report back: overall exposure, concentration risks, current drawdown vs. maximum allowed, and
              recommended adjustments. The persona is configured to be the team's voice of caution.
            </p>
            <div class="op-persona">
              <strong>Powered by:</strong> Jennie's persona (portfolio risk + position sizing)
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- How to Replicate -->
      <section class="article-section">
        <h2>How to Replicate This Setup</h2>
        <p>
          You don't need a 4-person team to benefit from this approach. Even as a solo trader or developer,
          you can create multiple personas for different tasks. Here's the basic blueprint:
        </p>

        <div class="steps-list">
          <div class="rep-step">
            <div class="rep-step-num">01</div>
            <div class="rep-step-content">
              <h3>Install OpenClaw and connect Telegram</h3>
              <p>Follow the <a href="/guide/install">install guide</a> and <a href="/guide/telegram">Telegram guide</a>. Get your base setup working before adding complexity.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="rep-step">
            <div class="rep-step-num">02</div>
            <div class="rep-step-content">
              <h3>Define your use case persona</h3>
              <p>
                Create a SOUL.md that's specific to how you trade. Include your preferred indicators, your risk
                tolerance, the markets you focus on, and your decision-making framework.
                See the <a href="/guide/first-persona">persona guide</a> for templates.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="rep-step">
            <div class="rep-step-num">03</div>
            <div class="rep-step-content">
              <h3>Set up a second workspace for a different role</h3>
              <p>
                Create a second directory (e.g., <code>~/.openclaw/workspace-risk/</code>) with a different SOUL.md
                focused on risk management. You can run multiple OpenClaw instances pointing to different workspaces,
                each accessible through its own Telegram bot.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="rep-step">
            <div class="rep-step-num">04</div>
            <div class="rep-step-content">
              <h3>Build daily workflows</h3>
              <p>
                The team's secret weapon is consistency. Every morning they send structured updates to their AI and
                get structured briefings back. Make the AI part of your daily routine, not a last resort.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="goal-box">
          <div class="goal-icon">üéØ</div>
          <div>
            <strong>This is within your reach.</strong>
            The BlackPink setup uses exactly the same tools described in this guide. No special access, no secret
            features ‚Äî just OpenClaw, a good SOUL.md, and the discipline to use it consistently. If they can run a
            multi-persona trading operation from their phones, so can you.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="nav-buttons">
        <a href="/guide/first-persona" class="btn btn-outline">‚Üê Persona Guide</a>
        <a href="/guide/install" class="btn btn-primary">Start from the Beginning ‚Üí</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,107,53,0.1) 0%, transparent 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
  }
  .page-hero .badge { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 650px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .page-content { padding: 3rem 0 5rem; }
  .page-content .container { max-width: 860px; }

  .article-section { margin-bottom: 4rem; }
  .article-section h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-bottom: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .article-section p { line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .overview-box {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ov-num { display: block; font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent); line-height: 1; }
  .ov-label { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text2); margin-top: 0.4rem; display: block; }

  .team-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .team-member-card {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .team-member-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .member-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .member-avatar { font-size: 2.5rem; }
  .member-name { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.2rem; }
  .member-title { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--accent2); font-weight: 600; }
  .member-desc { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .member-ai-role { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text2); background: var(--bg3); padding: 0.6rem 0.85rem; border-radius: 6px; }
  .role-badge { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 0.25rem; }

  .operation-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .op-card {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .op-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent2); }
  .op-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .op-icon { font-size: 1.75rem; }
  .op-title { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; }
  .op-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .op-card p em { color: var(--accent2); font-style: italic; }
  .op-persona { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text2); }

  .steps-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .rep-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .rep-step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--accent);
    line-height: 1;
    width: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .rep-step-content h3 { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .rep-step-content p { font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; }

  .goal-box {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255,107,53,0.08), rgba(0,212,255,0.05));
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,107,53,0.3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text2);
  }
  .goal-icon { font-size: 2rem; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .nav-buttons {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
    padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .overview-box { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .team-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .overview-box { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
</style>
